The Amiyi-Akah community in Njaba Local Government Area of  Imo state would henceforth been bustling with football festivities after Lagos based businessman, Chief Chukwuemeka Durueze donated glittering  trophy to be competed annually. The trophy, named Ugwumba Unity Cup, was presented to the town’s paramount ruler, HRH Eze F.N Ahanotu, the Iyi 1 of Amiyi-Akah, by the President general of Amiyi-Akah Town Union, Chief Vincent Odinaka Egbuchilem, and Chief Julius Ezeta Ezenwata. The competition, according to the donor,  was initiated to foster unity among the villages that make up Amiyi-Akah Autonomous Community and discovery of  talents in the grassroots.